node.text: Porsche is in the minds of many the ultimate sports car brand. Its cars – especially its legendary 911 – blend high performance with quality construction and even a solid reputation for dependability. But the brand that made its name with small nimble two-door sports cars ruffled feathers in the automotive world when it tried its hand at a four-door sport utility vehicle, the Cayenne. Today, SUVs make up a huge chunk of Porsche’s sales. The brand is now entering the race toward electrification – but this time the innovator is playing catch-up to others.

node.title: How Porsche went from sports cars to SUVs ... and EVs

node.text: It’s taken over two years, but these days Jeremy Mateo is finally feeling at home. Mateo, 27, is a real estate broker in Honolulu, Hawaii, and bought his first condo on Oahu island right before the coronavirus pandemic in March 2020. Over the course of a year he saved $60,000 for a down payment and worked toward his goal of buying his “dream home.” Then he spent another year renovating and furnishing his place. The last of his furniture arrived in spring 2021, finally closing the chapter on his homebuying journey. Here’s how Mateo bought his one-bedroom condo for $560,000. (With @CNBCMakeIt)

node.title: This 27-year-old spent $100,000 renovating his $560,000 condo in Hawaii

node.text: Violence and mass shootings erupted over the weekend, and could continue. 274 mass shootings have occurred this year, with 304 dead, which is on pace for one of the most violent years in history. Here's what the country's outlook is.

node.title: Violence and mass shootings erupted over the weekend

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on July 31, 2021. May be an image of ocean and text that says 'The "world's most powerful tidal turbine" starts to export power to the grid EO CNBC'.

node.text:
Dubbed “the world’s most powerful,” a tidal turbine weighing 680 metric tons has started grid-connected power generation at the European Marine Energy Centre in Orkney, an archipelago located north of mainland Scotland.⁠
⁠
The news marks another major step forward for the U.K.’s nascent marine energy sector. It’s expected that the turbine, which is 74-meters long, will “operate in the waters off Orkney for the next 15 years” and have “the capacity to meet the annual electricity demand of around 2,000 UK homes.”⁠
⁠
Details on how the turbine will generate so-called green hydrogen at the link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on July 31, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, office and text that says 'Here are your best money moves while the Fed keeps rates near zero CNBC'.

node.text:
The Federal Reserve on Wednesday said it would keep its benchmark interest rate near zero. But with inflation on the rise, this low-interest rate environment will not last.⁠
⁠
Although the federal funds rate — which is what banks charge one another for short-term borrowing — is not the rate that consumers pay, the Fed’s moves still affect the borrowing and saving rates they see every day. The Fed’s historically low borrowing rates make it easier to access cheaper loans, but also make it less desirable to hoard cash.⁠
⁠
For a breakdown of how consumers can take advantage of these easy monetary policies while they last, visit the link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on July 31, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Ponzi schemer Bernie Madoff earned $710 for almost 3,000 hours of prison work CNBC'.

node.text:
Some people might argue that Bernie Madoff was grossly overpaid even at just 24 cents per hour for working as an orderly in prison.⁠
⁠
Madoff, the late Ponzi scheme king who ripped off thousands of people for billions of dollars, earned just $710 after almost 3,000 hours of work while serving 12 years in a North Carolina federal prison before dying of kidney failure in April, newly released records show.⁠
⁠
Details on why at one point a supervisor noted he “needs closer supervision than most,” and was “not very dependable" at the link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on July 31, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Marlboro maker Philip Morris says it could stop selling cigarettes in Britain within 10 years CNBC'.

node.text:
Tobacco group Philip Morris International has reportedly said it plans to stop selling cigarettes in the U.K. in 10 years’ time.⁠
⁠
It could bring an end to the cigarette maker’s flagship Marlboro brand and comes two years after the U.K. government said it wanted to end smoking in England by 2030.⁠
⁠
Details on why the company's CEO says he wants "to allow this company to leave smoking behind” at the link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on July 30, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Here's how much Olympic athletes earn for winning medals PHILIPPINES CNBC'.

node.text:
The Philippines clinched its first ever gold medal in Tokyo this week, making Filipino weightlifter Hidilyn Diaz the country’s first Olympic gold medalist.⁠
⁠
As a reward for her historic achievement, Diaz will reportedly receive at least 33 million Philippine pesos (around $600,000) from the Philippine Sports Commission as well as the country’s top businessmen. She has also been offered two homes and free flights for life, according to reports.⁠
⁠
How much do medalists from the U.S. and other countries win? Link in bio to find out.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on July 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Amazon delivery companies routinely tell drivers to bypass safety inspections ៣. CNBC'.

node.text:
Amazon delivery companies around the U.S. are instructing workers to bypass daily inspections intended to make sure vans are safe to drive.⁠
⁠
Amazon requires contracted delivery drivers to inspect their vehicles at the beginning and end of their shift as a safety precaution. But some drivers say they’re pressured to ignore damage and complete the inspections as quickly as possible, so that delivery companies can avoid taking vans off the road. If delivery companies take a van off the road, they risk forfeiting valuable package routes and drivers may lose a shift.⁠
⁠
Read about how delivery drivers say flagging an issue can lose them a shift at the link in bio. (With @Fang)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on July 30, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Trump tax returns must be released by IRS to Congress, DOJ says CNBC'.

node.text:
🚨 BREAKING. 🚨⁠
⁠
The income tax returns of former President Donald Trump must be released by the IRS to Congress, the Department of Justice said Friday.⁠
⁠
The DOJ’s Office of Legal Counsel said in an opinion that the House Ways and Means Committee had made a request with a legitimate legislative purpose to see Trump’s tax returns, by saying the committee is assessing how the IRS audits presidents’ tax returns.⁠
⁠
Read the full story at the link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on July 30, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'CDC warns that delta variant is as contagious as chickenpox and may make people sicker than original Covid CNBC'.

node.text:
“The war has changed."⁠
⁠
The CDC warned House lawmakers Thursday that the new delta variant sweeping across the country is as contagious as chickenpox, has a longer transmission window than the original Covid-19 strain and may make older people sicker, even if they’ve been fully vaccinated, according to a copy of the document reviewed by CNBC and authenticated by the U.S. agency.⁠
⁠
Details on how the variant behaves “uniquely differently from past strains of the virus" at the link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on July 29, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says '"We are dealing with a different virus now." Dr. Dr. Anthony Fauci CNBC'.

node.text:
“We are dealing with a different virus now.”⁠
⁠
That’s what Dr. Anthony Fauci, White House chief medical advisor, told NPR this week about the Covid delta variant.⁠
⁠
“This is not the original virus that we were dealing with. This has different capabilities much more efficient in transmitting from person to person,” he said, explaining why the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention’s changed its mask guidelines.⁠
⁠
Fauci said the CDC reversed its mask guidance on Tuesday — recommending that fully vaccinated people go back to wearing masks indoors in places where there are high transmission rates — because delta is now the dominant strain in the U.S.⁠
⁠
What measures can you take to prevent getting the delta variant? Link in bio. (With @CNBCMakeIt)⁠

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on July 29, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Mark Zuckerberg thinks Facebook will profit by building a "metaverse' CNBC'.

node.text:
It’s either the next evolution of the internet or the latest corporate buzzword to get investors excited over some nebulous innovation that may not even come to pass over the next decade.⁠
⁠
Either way, tech companies — primarily Facebook — are increasingly boosting the concept of the “metaverse,” the classic sci-fi term for a virtual world you can live, work and play inside. If you’ve seen the movie “Ready Player One,” you have a pretty good idea of what the metaverse is: Strap on a set of computerized glasses, and you’re transported into a digital universe where anything is possible.⁠
⁠
How does Facebook plan to profit off of CEO Mark Zuckerberg's vision to pivot Facebook from a social media company to a metaverse company in the coming years? Link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on July 29, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, car and text that says 'Grand jury indicts Trevor Milton, founder of electric carmaker Nikola, on three counts of fraud CNBC NIKOLA'.

node.text:
A federal grand jury charged Nikola founder Trevor Milton with three counts of criminal fraud for lying about “nearly all aspects of the business” to bolster stock sales of the electric vehicle start-up, according to an indictment unsealed Thursday.⁠
⁠
The U.S. Attorney’s Office in Manhattan accused the 39-year-old billionaire, who resigned as chairman in September, with two counts of securities fraud, including making false statements about the company, and wire fraud.⁠
⁠
Details on how the indictment impacted Nikola stock at the link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on July 29, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, standing and text that says 'u.S. GDP increased at 6.5% pace in the second quarter, well below expectations அမய CNBC'.

node.text:
The U.S. economy rose at a disappointing rate in the second quarter –– a sign that the U.S. has escaped the shackles of the Covid-19 pandemic, but still has more work to do.⁠
⁠
GDP accelerated 6.5% on an annualized basis. That was slightly better than the 6.3% gain in the first quarter, which was revised down narrowly. While that would have been strong prior to the pandemic, the gain was considerably less than the 8.4% Dow Jones estimate.⁠
⁠
Even though GDP rose at a weaker rate than expected in Q2, it's likely to be the high point of the pandemic recovery. Read why at the link in bio.
